That's right, pour it on. Talk me out of it.

1467
01:54:57,686 --> 01:55:00,107
I called Mama.
She was so happy, she cried.

1468
01:55:00,181 --> 01:55:02,765
She wants you to have
her wedding gown. It's white lace.

1469
01:55:02,837 --> 01:55:05,902
Osgood, I can't get married
in your mother's dress.

1470
01:55:07,411 --> 01:55:10,574
She and I, we are not built the same way.

1471
01:55:10,643 --> 01:55:13,130
- We can have it altered.
- Oh no, you don't.

1472
01:55:14,514 --> 01:55:17,677
Osgood, I'm gonna level with you.
We can't get married at all.

1473
01:55:17,746 --> 01:55:19,119
Why not?

1474
01:55:19,185 --> 01:55:20,526
Well...

1475
01:55:20,592 --> 01:55:23,111
In the first place, I'm not a natural blonde.

1476
01:55:23,184 --> 01:55:24,907
Doesn't matter.

1477
01:55:24,975 --> 01:55:27,079
I smoke. I smoke all the time.

1478
01:55:27,151 --> 01:55:28,776
I don't care.

1479
01:55:28,847 --> 01:55:32,969
I have a terrible past. For three years
I've been living with a saxophone player.

1480
01:55:33,038 --> 01:55:34,793
I forgive you.

1481
01:55:36,397 --> 01:55:39,145
I can never have children.

1482
01:55:39,213 --> 01:55:43,041
- We can adopt some.
- You don't understand, Osgood.

1483
01:55:44,716 --> 01:55:46,691
- I'm a man.
- Well,

1484
01:55:46,759 --> 01:55:48,578
